PAObank secures insurance agency licence


PAO Bank Limited (PAObank) has received an Insurance Agency Licence from the Insurance Authority and signed strategic partnership agreements with China Ping An Insurance (Hong Kong) Company Limited (PAHK) and FWD Hong Kong (FWD). 

The bank is introducing general and life insurance services to enhance its bancassurance offerings for retail banking customers.  
PAObank’s partnership with PAHK will provide general insurance products, including motor, travel, and home insurance. 

Meanwhile, its collaboration with FWD expands on their previous work on Hong Kong's first bank-insurance “Commercial Data Interchange” (CDI) project, now extending into retail banking with life insurance products.  

The bank is integrating financial technology and API technology to connect with insurance platforms, allowing customers to purchase insurance online with a streamlined process.  

